The former chairman of Revenue Mobilization, Allocation and Fiscal Commission (RMAFC), Hamman Tukur, an engineer, is dead. Sources close to his family said the he died in Kaduna on yesterday morning. He will be buried in Kaduna according to Islamic rites. He was at various times Rector, Kaduna Polytechnic, Kaduna, Managing Director of the defunct National Electricity Power Authority (NEPA), and permanent secretary at the Federal Ministries of Power,Â  Steel, and Petroleum. He is survived by a wife and children. 